Testing #19044:

Not sure if I undertstood the mergin of args correctly
```json
{
    "version": "0.1.0",
    "showOutput": "always",
    
    "tasks": [
        {
            "taskName": "list",
            "command": "ls",
            "args": [ "-X"],
            "linux": {
                "command": "ls",
                "args": [ "-l"],
                "isShellCommand": true
            }
        }       
    ],
    "_runner": "terminal" 
}
```

Shouldn't this (on linux) run `ls -X -l` ?
It seems only `ls -l` is used

Testing #19044
```json
{
    "version": "0.1.0",
    "showOutput": "always",
    
    "tasks": [
        {
            "taskName": "list",
            "command": "ls",
            "options": {
                "cwd": "./.."
            },
            "linux": {
                "command": "ls",
                "args": [ "-l"],
                "isShellCommand": true
            }
        }       
    ],
    "_runner": "terminal" 
}
```
When executing this, the following message is written to the output view:
The task list is a shell command and specifies arguments. To ensure correct command line quoting please merge args into the command.

The output is in the terminal.
Maybe better everything in the terminal?
Also I'm not really sure what the message means. Maybe that information should better be shown in the task.json.
